    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-08-23T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-08-23T05:00:00-05:00" n="349"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d349">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/23713: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France (<persName type="from">Tuck</persName>)
                        to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vichy</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-23T12:00:00+02:00"
                            >August 23, 1942—noon.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 24—5:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1229. For Atherton.<note n="38" xml:id="d349fn38">Ray Atherton, Acting Chief of
                        the Division of European Affairs.</note> Our 1182, August 12, 5 p.m.<note
                        n="39" xml:id="d349fn39">Not printed.</note> Following message for Murphy
                    was delivered by person mentioned in reference message above.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“Your friend from Algiers after another interview yesterday with the chief of
                        resistance and with your common friend ‘the bather of suffren’ has nothing
                        to add to his last message.</p>
                    <p>It appears possible to be ready in metropolitan France by next March or
                        April. Africa, however, should receive equipment and material by October. It
                        is more urgent than ever that you furnish us with the arms and equipment for
                        North Africa and that conversations be held in Africa between French staff
                        officers and an American staff officer.”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tuck</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
